<%- include('_top', { appName: 'ClientPortal Shop', pageTitle: 'Username Check', theme: 'injection', tag: '/labs/sqli-time-blind' }) %>
<div class="lab-card">
  <h1>Username availability check</h1>
  <p>No result is shown either way -- registration just checks silently. Time your requests.</p>
  <form method="POST" action="/labs/sqli-time-blind/lookup">
    <label>Username</label>
    <input name="username" value="<%= username %>" placeholder="guest">
    <button type="submit">Check</button>
  </form>
  <% if (error) { %><div class="lab-alert error"><%= error %></div><% } %>
  <% if (elapsedMs !== null) { %><div class="lab-alert info">Query executed in <strong><%= elapsedMs %>ms</strong>.</div><% } %>
</div>
<div class="lab-card">
  <h2>Force a delay</h2>
  <p class="lab-meta">SQLite has no <code>SLEEP()</code>, but a recursive CTE that counts to a few million rows takes real, measurable time. Try injecting a condition that only runs a heavy query when a guessed character from the <code>sqli_secrets</code> table (label <code>time-flag</code>) is correct.</p>
  <p class="lab-meta">A big jump in response time confirms the guess. Repeat per character, then submit your reconstructed secret:</p>
  <form method="POST" action="/labs/sqli-time-blind/check">
    <label>Reconstructed secret</label>
    <input name="answer" placeholder="ZDS{...}">
    <button type="submit">Verify</button>
  </form>
  <% if (checkResult) { %>
    <div class="lab-alert <%= checkResult.correct ? 'success' : 'error' %>">
      <% if (checkResult.correct) { %>Correct! Flag: <span class="lab-flag"><%= checkResult.flag %></span><% } else { %>Not quite -- keep extracting.<% } %>
    </div>
  <% } %>
</div>
<%- include('_bottom') %>
